The paper presents a model for a Choquet integral for arbitrary finite set systems, which is a topic in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also discusses a Monge-type algorithm for computing the Choquet integral for intersection systems, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of capacities on union-closed systems, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and social choice theory (cs.SI).
